o’s HEPA filter and sealed casing do an excellent job of trapping dust and allergens and not releasing them back into the air. This is a real plus if you have allergies or asthma.","The Bolero uses a true HEPA (high efficiency particulate air) filter, rather than one that is “HEPA-like.” As a result, it is capable of capturing and holding 99.99 percent of all particles, even those as small as 0.3 microns. HEPA filters meet certain high air filtration standards set by the U.S. Department of Energy.","Additionally, the Miele Bolero’s spring-loaded dust bag is automatically sealed shut when you open the door to replace the bag, sparing you from inhaling or even touching materials that could aggravate respiratory or other health problems. Another filter captures incoming dirt and trash fragments to protect the motor.","The dust bag itself is large, which lets you use it for long intervals before replacing it. It can hold 5.4 quarts of dust, dirt and anything else it sucked up from your household floors, furniture, venetian blinds, bookshelves, stairs and dust-collecting objects. This vacuum uses its own patented AirClean dust bag that has nine filtration layers, intended to capture even minute particulates and bits of rubbish.","You also will like the fact that the vacuum’s patented Air Clean filter has an active charcoal section included with it to absorb unpleasant smells. For many homeowners who have pets or who are particularly susceptible to odors, this is a highly valuable characteristic.","You undoubtedly will be pleased to find the Miele Bolero features a 1,200-watt Vortex motor with powerful airflow and automatic control settings that adjust the machine’s power according to whatever surface you are cleaning. If you prefer, you also can elect to use a manual rotary dial on the handle to change the suction power to six different settings.","The vacuum actually operates using two motors. The secondary motor runs the vacuum’s roller brush at 4,800 rpm. The brush also has automatic height adjustments built into the machine. These routinely raise or lower the roller brush for you to suit different types of flooring as you move through the house. The roller brush also turns off quickly while the suction keeps going when the vacuum moves from carpeting to bare floors. This helps you avoid scratching hardwood or damaging other delicate floor coverings.","You will no doubt appreciate the Bolero’s motor protection indicator, which likely will save you aggravation and save the machine if you run into that all-too-common household mishap: vacuuming up a sock. The indicator device automatically shuts off the roller brush and turns on a red or yellow light, letting you know that there is some kind of blockage.","There are other lights as well: one alerts you that it is time change the bag while another lets you know it is time to change the HEPA filter. The Miele Bolero also has a safety shut-off device that automatically turns off the vacuum if it begins to overheat.","You will find the ergonomically designed handles for operating and carrying the vacuum are comfortable and will take a load off your joints and back, even while carrying the vacuum up stairs. The Miele Bolero also presents another useful benefit: an anti-tipping device that keeps the vacuum from toppling over. This is especially worthwhile when you are busy reaching up to do above- the- floor cleaning using the extra tools such as the dusting brush or crevice nozzle."]},"id":"ef6bf94b-f1bd-4441-aa1d-6c9440717eeb","type":"text"},{"data":{"text":"Price"},"id":"0608f26e-7b8c-42aa-a226-8a44d9521a8a","type":"heading"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["You will find a generous 39-foot power cord on the Miele Bolero that lets you clean one space after another without the nuisance of having to keeping plugging and unplugging the vacuum. In many cases, the extra-long power cord means you can plug in the vacuum itself in one room and easily clean others.","Although it weighs 22 pounds, the Bolero possesses a specially designed swivel neck that lets you smoothly move the torso of the vacuum around in all directions. Believe it or not, you can even lay this upright vacuum flat on the floor with the body of the vacuum sticking up only six inches, so you can easily clean under beds and furniture.","If you push a foot switch, the rear wheels move up into the body of the vacuum itself, which allows easy, gliding movements as you clean under and around chairs, tables or other furniture in your home. The front castor wheels rotate 360 degrees and are made of high-quality rubber that leaves no marks on hard surfaces. A row of eight LED lights in the headlight area makes it easy to maneuver in dark hallways or other dimly lit spaces. This vacuum also has a rubber bumper to guard against dinging your furniture.","This product is durable and the vacuum cleaner body is made of sturdy ABS (acrylonitrile butadiene styrene) plastic, which is the type of plastic used to manufacture such things as football helmets and boats. The Bolero upright vacuum has been tested to last an average of 20 years when used for residential cleaning for 45 minutes each week while set at the highest settings."]},"id":"d237e84f-55bb-4982-8d17-9faa84abab8e","type":"text"},{"data":{"text":"Convenience &amp; Design"},"id":"6c28b2fe-bb08-415d-a41f-714d1853e1a0","type":"heading"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["You will find clearing cobwebs off curtain rods or dust off a ceiling fan is surprisingly easy with Bolero’s hose and telescopic wand, which combined gives you a 15-foot reach. Add that to the 39-foot electrical cord, and you have a remarkably large 54-foot cleaning radius. <br/>This vacuum cleaner comes with a dusting brush for cleaning delicate surfaces, an extra-long crevice nozzle for such things as cleaning between sofa cushions, and an upholstery brush that works well on furniture and quickly snaps up pet hair. The hose and all the tools fit nicely into specially designed areas on the vacuum cleaner’s back."]},"id":"3104c875-b669-4a82-9201-daabd8cff3fd","type":"text"},{"data":{"text":"Design Extras"},"id":"d258439f-be98-42e3-9217-4c44f792b7b1","type":"heading"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["The Bolero provides a seven-year warranty on the motors and a one-year warranty for parts and labor. You also can contact the company via email and phone, and the company’s web site offers a search function allowing you to locate authorized Miele dealers who can provide service and repairs. The web site also displays videos and photo slide shows depicting the features of this type of Miele vacuum."]},"id":"be5d95bd-c9e2-43dc-abf0-1d4ac8abdfc8","type":"text"},{"data":{"text":"Summary"},"id":"aa317e20-7a72-4384-8f66-7c98d0727eea","type":"heading"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["The Miele Bolero is an outstanding upright vacuum cleaner that is flexible, powerful and versatile enough to clean just about any home imaginable. It is probably one of the best vacuum cleaners on the market today. It clearly warrants the top spot for its abundance of first-rate features, long warranty, extremely large cleaning radius and excellent filtration."]},"id":"0a7635d1-640d-4d93-87dc-46c1ee8c1f42","type":"text"}]],"body":null,"legacyId":"product_review_page_52175","url":"/miele-bolero-review","authors":[{"email":"","slug":"angie-parkinson","url":"/author/angie-parkinson","dateCreated":"2019-04-17T20:46:58Z","name":"Angie Parkinson","dateModified":"2019-04-17T20:46:58Z","id":"4Pu3Dbh8P3CR8CNSJRVPZP","dateImported":null,"site":"toptenreviews"}],"territories":["US","GB"],"companies":[],"dateCreated":"2011-02-16T16:24:16Z","datePublished":"2011-02-16T16:24:16Z","name":"Miele Bolero","synopsis":"Editor’s Note: This product has been removed from our side-by-side comparison because it has been replaced by another product.","review":{"rating":100,"verdict":"Miele designed this top-notch product with the idea that it will last 20 years.","pros":["This Miele Bolero is a strong, flexible machine loaded with